article_title: Texas doctors give Obamacare bad grades
article_text: To continue reading this story, you will need to be a digital subscriber to HoustonChronicle.com.

og.description: More than 36 percent of Texas doctors gave the Affordable Care Act an F  "as a vehicle for healthcare reform" and 22 percent gave it a D,  according to a comissioned by The Physicians Foundation.  Nationally, just under 25 percent of respondents gave the act an F.  Twenty-one percent gave it a D.
